The 2022 Mock-Unified Tertiary Education Examination (Mock-UTME) has been scheduled to hold on Saturday, 9th April 2022. Recall that the Mock-UTME had earlier been scheduled to hold onSaturday,16th April 2022. The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB), in its weekly bulletin, explained that the change was due to the realization that 16th April 2022, earlier chosen, is Easter Saturday, a day celebrated by the Christian faith as a Holy Saturday as it ends the Lenten Season falls on the day before Easter Sunday. 2023 Election: Atiku Cannot Be Trusted – Afegbua Blows Hot Electoral Act 2022: Buhari Validates Anti-Rigging Device —… It would be recalled that the Board was to begin its registration for 2022/23UTME/DE exercise on Saturday, 12th February 2022, but had to push the exercise to Saturday, 19th of February, 2022. The one-week extension had similarly affected the date for the Mock-UTME which also had to be rescheduled. “The Board, as a responsive organization, would at all times, continue to act in the best interests of Nigerians. “Therefore, all candidates who wish to register early to sit the Mock UTME are to kindly note the change of date,” the Board stated in the statement Meanwhile, the Board has expressed delight that its partnership with the National Identity Management Commission (NIMC) is yieldingdesired results as the process which, by all indications, was deemed impracticable in 2019 and had to be shelved, was re-introduced in 2020 with little hitches. JAMB said the registration process has become seamless in all ramifications in 2021 and now improved in 2022. The board said in 10 ten days of the 2022 UTME/DE Registration, it has registered 236,206 candidates.